    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-06-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-06-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="397"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Comly</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-06-02">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">June</hi> 2, 1882</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Comly</hi>: Permit me again to recur to your
                    dispatch No. 217 of the 8th ultimo, touching the possible tendency of political
                    events on the Hawaiian Islands, and to express to you my appreciation of your
                    vigilance in the matter.</p>
                <p>In view of the very large interests which are held in those islands by our
                    citizens, many of whom are residents of the Pacific coast, I have thought it
                    expedient to furnish for the confidential information of the honorables John F.
                    Miller and James T. Farley, Senators of the United States from the State of
                    California, a copy of your dispatch without its accompaniments, and a copy of it
                    entire has been sent to the Secretary of the Navy.</p>
                <p>Very truly, yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Freb’k T. Frelinghuysen.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
